<p><a href="https://dustri.org/b/images/no_fundraising_2018.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img alt="Banner of the fund-raising campaign" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/FLA0AkwxzPQmWSK54JAN0GrEXGNP2siTLJroIq8YB1E=/aHR0cHM6Ly9kdXN0cmkub3JnL2IvaW1hZ2VzL25vX2Z1bmRyYWlzaW5nXzIwMTgucG5n" loading="lazy"/></a></p>
<p><a href="https://nos-oignons.net" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Nos Oignons</a> is a 10 years old French non-profit association living on
donations, dedicated to running <a href="https://torproject.org" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Tor exit nodes</a> in France, to improve the diversity of the network.
A bit like
<a href="https://emeraldonion.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Emerald Onions</a> in Seatle,
<a href="https://www.zwiebelfreunde.de/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Zwiebelfreunde</a> in Germany,
<a href="https://applied-privacy.net/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">The Foundation for Applied Privacy</a> in Austria,
<a href="https://artikel10.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Artikel10</a> in the Netherlands,
<a href="https://www.dfri.se/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">DFRI</a> in Sweden,
…</p>
<p>Full-disclosure, I&#39;m part of its administrative council, and the system administrator team.</p>
<p>A <em>bit less</em> than 1 on 100 connections are going through <a href="https://nos-oignons.net/Services/index.en.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">one of our 14
relays</a>, we&#39;re providing a
capacity of symmetric 600Mbit/s to the network and are amongst the
<a href="https://nusenu.github.io/OrNetStats/w/family/53c61483eb350147079478805df9b02a40149eab1d51b1382140fdae9616eaa1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">top20</a> exit families. To
keep our machines running, we need money: we&#39;re <a href="https://nos-oignons.net/Actualit%C3%A9s/20221017_rapports_2021_2022/index.en.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">still
afloat, but barely.</a>;
thanks to recurring donations, but we would like to have some margin and to
spawn a new relays: a single machine costs us, per day, around 30€.</p>
<p>This is why we&#39;re doing a <a href="https://nos-oignons.net/Actualit%C3%A9s/20230529_Campagne_et_video/index.en.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">donation
campaign</a> in 2023: more
sustainability, resilience, and hopefully new exit nodes! We even did a video
for the occasion:</p>
<p><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/uroe-xe0tcM" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups" loading="lazy"></iframe></p><p>Of course, goodies as
in &#34;postcards and posters&#34; for you should you give more than respectively 10€
and 50€. Our yearly budget is about 12,000€, and a bit more than 80% of it
goes directly to pay relays, you can find all the details
<a href="https://nos-oignons.net/%C3%80_propos/index.en.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">here</a>.</p>
<p>Help us to help the tor network in France, <a href="https://nos-oignons.net/Donnez/index.en.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">donate to Nos Oignons</a>!</p>